The paper focuses on software testing and optimization, which are topics commonly found in the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The use of search-based strategies and tabu search also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method through experiments and assesses the quality of the results, which aligns with the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
